3#ifndef __DRM_GEM_CMA_HELPER_H__
4#define __DRM_GEM_CMA_HELPER_H__
5
6#include <drm/drmP.h>
7#include <drm/drm_gem.h>
8
9/**
10 * struct drm_gem_cma_object - GEM object backed by CMA memory allocations
11 * @base: base GEM object
12 * @paddr: physical address of the backing memory
13 * @sgt: scatter/gather table for imported PRIME buffers
14 * @vaddr: kernel virtual address of the backing memory
15 */
16struct drm_gem_cma_object {
17 struct drm_gem_object base;
18#ifdef __NetBSD__
19 bus_dma_tag_t dmat;
20 bus_dma_segment_t dmasegs[1];
21 bus_size_t dmasize;
22 bus_dmamap_t dmamap;
23#else
24 dma_addr_t paddr;
25#endif
26 struct sg_table *sgt;
27
28 /* For objects with DMA memory allocated by GEM CMA */
29 void *vaddr;
30};
31
32static inline struct drm_gem_cma_object *
33to_drm_gem_cma_obj(struct drm_gem_object *gem_obj)
34{
35 return container_of(gem_obj, struct drm_gem_cma_object, base);
36}
37
38/* free GEM object */
39void drm_gem_cma_free_object(struct drm_gem_object *gem_obj);
